⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Lazarus Long
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Lazarus Long:H1:af76b0⟧

WHO   — Woodrow Wilson Smith, born 1912, the longest-lived human being — a product of the Howard Families' breeding for longevity who simply refused, across two thousand years, to die.
WHAT  — The wandering immortal at the centre of Heinlein's Future History — rogue, pioneer, captain, and at last patriarch of his own line through time itself.
WHERE — From the Howard Families on Earth to a thousand colonies and back through time to 1916 Kansas City.
WHY   — To keep living, keep moving, keep loving — because curiosity outlasts everything, and "the only way to stay young is to keep doing dangerous things."
HOW   — By rejuvenation, by cunning, by leaving any world that grew too tame; and finally by a time machine that let him become his own ancestry.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  There ain't no such thing as a free lunch — and there ain't no such thing as enough time.

